A rare megamouth shark washed up on a beach dead in the Philippines this week, wildlife officials have said. 

The 15-foot shark, a Megachasma pelagios (giant mouth of the deep), was discovered dead on the beach in Marigondon, Pio Duran, in Albay province. 

It is only the 60th megamouth shark seen in the world, according to marine biologist Christopher Bird.

