Most have been found in Japan, the Philippines and Taiwan, but the first confirmed megamouth shark sighting came in 1976, when a deep-sea anchor accidentally caught one near Hawaii.

A megamouth shark can reach to a maximum length of 17 feet and have a life span of up to 100 years, according to Reuters.

The species lives in deep waters but rises towards the surface at night to feed or eat plankton.   

